</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="152" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[812,1452,512,632]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,959,512,537]" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,929,513,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">Etymology</emphasis>
. –
</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<emphasis box="[1146,1210,513,536]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">longi-</emphasis>
, meaning longer, and the Latin 
<emphasis box="[924,992,545,568]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">pterus</emphasis>
, meaning fin. In reference to the longer pectoral fin, pelvic fin and caudal fin, distinguished from 
<taxonomicName class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudexostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brachysoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">P. brachysoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[997,1160,609,632]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Sisoridae" genus="Pseudexostoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Siluriformes" pageId="5" pageNumber="152" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis box="[997,1160,609,632]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="152">P. yunnanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
